# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# aeon-music-maker — environment variables
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values. The Python CLI reads
# these via os.environ at runtime (no config file parsing — pure env).
#
# How to use:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   $EDITOR .env
#   ./setup.sh           # validates everything resolves
#   python scripts/music_maker.py --prompt "..." -o track.flac
#
# If a variable is COMMENTED OUT below, it's optional and the script falls
# back to a sensible default. If UNCOMMENTED with no value, the script will
# fail on startup.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. ComfyUI server endpoint  (REQUIRED if not using the default)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is the HTTP URL where your ComfyUI server is listening. The CLI
# never spawns ComfyUI — it only sends workflow JSONs to /prompt and polls
# /history for results.
#
# ─── If ComfyUI runs on the SAME machine as this script (LOCAL MODE): ───
#   COMFYUI_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8188
#
# ─── If ComfyUI runs on a DIFFERENT machine (REMOTE MODE): ──────────────
#   Option A — direct HTTP to remote IP:
#     COMFYUI_URL=http://192.168.x.x:8188
#     # Make sure your firewall allows the connection. ComfyUI defaults to
#     # binding 127.0.0.1 only — start it with --listen 0.0.0.0 if remote.
#
#   Option B — SSH tunnel (more secure, no firewall change):
#     # On your local machine, before running this CLI:
#     #   ssh -L 8188:127.0.0.1:8188 user@remote-comfyui-host
#     # Then leave COMFYUI_URL at the local default:
#     COMFYUI_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8188
#
COMFYUI_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8188


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. ComfyUI install root  (OPTIONAL — only if you want output in shared tree)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# If set, the script writes output FLACs to ${COMFYUI_ROOT}/output/music/.
# Otherwise it falls back to ./output/music/ relative to this repo.
#
# Set this ONLY when:
#   - ComfyUI runs on the SAME machine as this script (LOCAL MODE), AND
#   - You want generated tracks alongside ComfyUI's other outputs.
#
# In REMOTE MODE, leave this UNSET — the local repo's `./output/` is fine.
# (You can't write directly into the remote ComfyUI's output/ over HTTP;
# the model output files come back via the API and we save them locally.)
#
# Example for local Windows ComfyUI install:
# COMFYUI_ROOT=C:/Users/yourname/Documents/ComfyUI
#
# Example for local Linux/macOS:
# COMFYUI_ROOT=/home/yourname/ComfyUI


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. Output directory  (OPTIONAL — overrides COMFYUI_ROOT/output)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where generated FLACs land. If unset, defaults to ${COMFYUI_ROOT}/output
# when COMFYUI_ROOT is set, otherwise ./output/ in this repo.
#
# OUTPUT_DIR=./my-tracks


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. Binary paths  (OPTIONAL — uses PATH lookup by default)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The script needs ffmpeg + ffprobe for transcoding and LUFS measurement.
# By default it uses whatever's on PATH. Override only if your binaries
# live elsewhere (e.g. compiled from source, or installed to non-standard
# location on Windows).
#
# Linux/macOS examples:
# FFMPEG=/usr/local/bin/ffmpeg
# FFPROBE=/usr/local/bin/ffprobe
#
# Windows example:
# FFMPEG=C:/ffmpeg/bin/ffmpeg.exe
# FFPROBE=C:/ffmpeg/bin/ffprobe.exe


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. ACE Step variant default  (OPTIONAL)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default --variant when the CLI flag is omitted. Choices:
#   xl_base       — full fp32, 50 steps APG chain. Highest quality. (DEFAULT)
#   xl_sft        — bf16 SFT, 45 steps APG. Slightly faster.
#   xl_base_sft   — merged base+SFT, simple KSampler. Fastest base-quality.
#   xl_turbo      — distilled fp16 turbo, 10 steps. Use for fast previews.
#   base_turbo    — smallest 4.8 GB turbo, 8 steps. Quickest, lowest quality.
#
# ACE_DEFAULT_VARIANT=xl_base


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. Mastering preset default  (OPTIONAL)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default --master when the CLI flag is omitted. Choices:
#   auto       — pick from prompt keywords (DEFAULT, recommended)
#   off        — disable mastering, keep raw ACE output
#   default | edm | trap | chill | orchestral | jazz
#
# MASTER_DEFAULT_PRESET=auto


# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. HuggingFace token  (OPTIONAL — only if downloading gated ACE Step models)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Some HuggingFace repositories require a token even for public read access.
# If `setup.sh` reports models as missing and you want it to download them,
# create a free account at huggingface.co, then:
#
#   1. Go to https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
#   2. Click "New token"
#   3. Name it (e.g. "aeon-music-maker"), give it "Read" access
#   4. Copy the token (starts with "hf_...") and paste below
#
# NOT required if you'll download models manually via web browser or use
# ComfyUI Manager.
#
# HF_TOKEN=hf_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
